headline_main: Transgender Lives: Your Stories: Katherine Harris

abstract: After a 2 month medical leave, I returned to work.  I was fired one week later, for "egregiously violating company policy".  Laws and a life in a liberal state weren't enough to protect me.  My life is too egregious a violation.

abstract: My despair had not been caused by the inequities of the world around me, but by my own willingness to sacrifice my true self in order to belong to it.
